Class ArgumentBuilder.MapArgumentBuilder<K,V>

    @NotThreadSafe
public static final class ArgumentBuilder.MapArgumentBuilder<K,V>
extends ArgumentBuilder<BUILDER,T>
    An intermediate builder used by ArgumentBuilder.asPropertyMap(). It's mainly used to switch the T argument of the previous builder to Map<K, T> and to indicate invalid call orders.

      • defaultValue

        public ArgumentBuilder.MapArgumentBuilder<K,V> defaultValue(Map<K,V> defaultKeyValues)
        Description copied from class: ArgumentBuilder
         Sets a default value to use for this argument. Overrides StringParser.defaultValue() which is used by default.
 Returned by ParsedArguments.get(Argument) when no argument was given.
 To create default values lazily see ArgumentBuilder.defaultValueSupplier(Supplier).
        Mutability:Remember that as Argument is Immutable this value should be so too if multiple argument parsings is going to take place. If mutability is wanted ArgumentBuilder.defaultValueSupplier(Supplier) should be used instead.
        Overrides:
        defaultValue in class ArgumentBuilder<ArgumentBuilder.MapArgumentBuilder<K,V>,Map<K,V>>
